{
  "title": "Packaging CLI Tools Using FastAPI in Python 3.12+",
  "summary": "This guide explains how to create and package Command Line Interface (CLI) tools using FastAPI, a modern web framework for building APIs in Python 3.12+.",

  "key_points": [
    "FastAPI can be used as a foundation for creating CLI tools in addition to its traditional API development.",
    "By utilizing the `typer` library, FastAPI can simplify CLI tool creation while maintaining the benefits of using FastAPI such as type hints and improved introspection.",
    "You will learn how to structure projects, implement command-line arguments, handle input/output, and finally package your CLI tool for distribution.",
  ],

  "code_examples": [
    {
      "language": "python",
      "code": "from fastapi import FastAPI\nfrom typer import Typer\napp = FastAPI()\ncli = Typer(app=app)\n# Define commands below..."
    },
    {
      "language": "python",
      "code": "def hello(ctx: Context):\n print('Hello World!')\ncli.command('hello', hello)\n"
    }
  ],

  "version_notes": [
    "This guide is specifically tailored for Python 3.12+, as FastAPI has added features and improvements since earlier versions.",
    "Make sure to install the latest version of FastAPI and typer using pip:"
  ],

  "caveats": [
    "Although this guide focuses on CLI tools, it's essential to understand that FastAPI is primarily an API framework. The examples provided demonstrate how you can use it for non-web applications.",
    "Ensure that your target platform supports both Python 3.12+ and the installed dependencies before distributing your CLI tool."
  ]
}
